        "disclaimer_gcdAUm": {
          "type": "disclaimer",
          "settings": {
            "disclaimer": "<p>1. Results observed in a limited study when Hydrafacial treatment was performed in combination with intense pulsed light (IPL) or Q-switched laser.</p><p>2. Results observed in a limited study when Hydrafacial treatment was performed in combination with non-ablative fractional laser and fractional radio frequency for facial rejuvenation.</p><p>3. Results observed in a limited study when Hydrafacial treatment was performed in combination with radio frequency and focused ultrasound for facial firming.</p><p>4. Results observed in a limited study when Hydrafacial treatment was performed in combination with fractional facial resurfacing with ablative fractional laser (CO2 or Erbium:YAG).</p><p>5. Data on file. HydraFacial, LLC</p><p>6. In a clinical study 24 hours after 1 Hydrafacial treatment with Hydralock HA booster. Based on Corneometer measurements of 38 participants before and 24 hours after treatment in a clinical study. Individual results may vary.</p><p>6*. Based on QuantifiCare skin analysis of 38 participants before, immediately after,<br/>and 24 hours post-treatment in a clinical study. Individual results may vary.</p><p>7. Participant perception of 10 female patients receiving 1 Hydrafacial treatment. Data on file Hydrafacial, LLC.</p><p>8. Based on Investigator assessment of 20 participants with mild to moderate acne who received 6 Clarifying Hydrafacial Treatments over 12 weeks. Individual results may vary.</p><p>9. Based on perception of 44 participants receiving a series of 3 Hydrafacial Keravive treatments with daily application of take-home peptide spray in between treatments for 20 weeks.</p>"
